DESCRIPTION = "<h2> Exploratory Factor Analysis (EFA) </h2>\n<h3> Description </h3>\n<div>\nEFA identifies latent factors that explain correlations among observed variables. Options include extraction method (ML or Principal Axis using the correlation matrix), \nand common rotations (Varimax, Quartimax, Equamax, Promax). The analysis also reports KMO and Bartlett\u2019s tests, eigenvalues, communalities/uniquenesses,\nand (for oblique rotations) factor correlations and both pattern and structure matrices.\n</div>\n<h3> Inputs </h3>\n<div>\n<b>Variables:</b> Numeric/ordinal variables to analyse.<br>\n<b>Number of factors:</b> How many latent factors to extract.<br>\n<b>Method:</b> Maximum Likelihood (ML) or Principal Axis (PCA-based approximation).<br>\n<b>Rotation:</b> None / Varimax / Quartimax / Equamax (orthogonal); Promax (oblique).<br>\n<b>Kaiser normalization:</b> Optionally normalize before rotation.\n</div>\n"
